ZH: 他总是用花言巧语来哄我。
EN: He always uses sweet words to coax me.

ZH: 不要被他的花言巧语迷惑了。
EN: Don't be deceived by his sweet talk.

ZH: 她被他的花言巧语所感动。
EN: She was touched by his sweet words.

ZH: 不要轻易相信别人的花言巧语。
EN: Don't easily believe in someone's sweet talk.

ZH: 他只会说花言巧语，却不会实际行动。
EN: He only knows how to speak sweet words, but never takes action.

ZH: 别听信他的花言巧语。
EN: Don't believe in his sweet talk.

ZH: 不要用花言巧语来欺骗别人。
EN: Don't deceive others with sweet words.

ZH: 他的花言巧语让我感到不舒服。
EN: His sweet talk makes me uncomfortable.

ZH: 别为了一句花言巧语就轻易相信别人。
EN: Don't easily believe in someone just because of sweet talk.

ZH: 她的花言巧语让人心醉。
EN: Her sweet talk makes people enchanted.

ZH: 别让他的花言巧语蒙蔽了你的双眼。
EN: Don't let his sweet talk blind your eyes.

ZH: 他用花言巧语来掩盖真相。
EN: He uses sweet talk to cover up the truth.

ZH: 不要被他的花言巧语蒙骗了。
EN: Don't be fooled by his sweet talk.

ZH: 她总是用花言巧语哄孩子开心。
EN: She always uses sweet talk to make the children happy.

ZH: 不要仅仅因为他的花言巧语而相信他。
EN: Don't just believe in him because of his sweet talk.

ZH: 他的花言巧语让我产生了怀疑。
EN: His sweet talk made me doubt.

ZH: 父母不要用花言巧语来教育孩子。
EN: Parents should not use sweet talk to educate children.

ZH: 她的花言巧语让他完全相信了她。
EN: Her sweet talk made him completely trust her.

ZH: 如果只有花言巧语而没有行动，那就是欺骗。
EN: If there are only sweet words without action, it is deception.
